headline: W.W. Grainger (NYSE:GWW) Posts Q3 Sales In Line With Estimates
summary: Maintenance and repair supplier W.W. Grainger (NYSE:GWW) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 6.1% year on year to $4.66 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $17.9 billion at the midpoint came in 0.7% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $10.21 per share was 2.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: GRAINGER REPORTS RESULTS FOR THE THIRD QUARTER 2025
summary: Grainger (NYSE: GWW) today reported results for the third quarter of 2025 with sales of $4.7 billion, up 6.1%, or 5.4% on a daily, constant currency basis, and adjusted diluted EPS of $10.21, up 3.4% compared to the third quarter of 2024.
